        <!-- ------------------------------------ Expired Vehicle Registration------------------------------------------ -->


        <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="profile12" aria-labelledby="profile-tab11">
            <div class="pensyl">
                <h3>Expired Vehicle Registration</h3>
            </div>

            <p>
                Driving with an expired registration is considered a second degree misdemeanor, punishable up to 60 days in the
                 county jail. Florida Statute 320.07 states your registration expires at midnight on the last day of 
                registration or extended registration period. A vehicle may not be operated unless the registration is 
                renewed. If your registration is expired less than 6 months it is a noncriminal moving violation. If your
                 registration is expired more than 6 months and it is your first offense it is a noncriminal moving violation.
                 However, if your registration is expired more than 6 months and it is not the first time, you will be 
                charged with this offense.
            </p>
